</ul>
<p><a name="Acquired_companies_and_studios" id="Acquired_companies_and_studios"></a></p>
<h4><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=DC_Comics&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: Acquired companies and studios">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Acquired companies and studios</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/All-American_Publications" title="All-American Publications">All-American Publications</a> (merged 1944)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Archie_Comics" title="Archie Comics">Archie Comics</a> (superhero properties licensed 1991-1993 as part of <a href="/wiki/Impact_Comics" title="Impact Comics">Impact Comics</a>, properties later acquired 2008)<sup id="cite_ref-15" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-15" title=""><span>[</span>16<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Charlton_Comics" title="Charlton Comics">Charlton Comics</a> (some properties acquired 1983)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Fawcett_Comics" title="Fawcett Comics">Fawcett Comics</a> (some properties licensed 1972, acquired early 1990s)<sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since November 2007" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Flex_Comix" title="Flex Comix">Flex Comix</a> (made investment in 2007; jointly owned with other companies)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Mad_(magazine)" title="Mad (magazine)">Mad magazine</a> (not owned, but assigned to DC's corporate control in the late 1990s. Both companies are part of Warner Bros. Entertainment)<sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since November 2007" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Quality_Comics" title="Quality Comics">Quality Comics</a> (some properties licensed 1956, later acquired)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/WaRP_Graphics" title="WaRP Graphics">WaRP Graphics</a> (properties licenced from 2003 to 2007)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Wildstorm" title="Wildstorm">WildStorm Productions</a> (properties acquired 1999)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Will_Eisner" title="Will Eisner">Will Eisner Library</a> (some properties licensed 2000)</li>
</ul>
